in\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The six-time Olympic medalist has opted to pull out of the competition while the International Federation for Equestrian Sports (FEI) investigates the incident, which occurred during a coaching session.\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.446324637908391e-30, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin is Britain's second-most decorated female Olympian.Announcing the news, she said in a statement: \\\"A video has emerged from four years ago which shows me making an error of judgement during a coaching session.Olympics 2024: Charlotte Dujardin has withdrawn from the games in Paris|GETTY\\\"Understandably, the International Federation for Equestrian Sports (FEI) is investigating and I have made the decision to withdraw from all competition - including the Paris Olympics - while this process takes place.\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 622, \"end\": 629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8003505741601429, \"rank\": 0.2494521781139064, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 842, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}, {\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.446324637908391e-30, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What happened was completely out of character and does not reflect how I train my horses or coach my pupils, however there is no excuse.\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am deeply ashamed and should have set a better example in that moment.\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am sincerely sorry for my actions and devastated that I have let everyone down, including Team GB, fans and sponsors.JUST IN:Emma Raducanu fans vent fury as Andy Murray confirms tennis retirement after Paris Olympics\\\"I will cooperate fully with the FEI, British Equestrian Federation and British Dressage during their investigations, and will not be commenting further until the process is complete.\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999997765962939, \"rank\": 1.9348865637905507e-07, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1459, \"end\": 1472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Raducanu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\"}, {\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"ht